section.section:
A member of the Ocean Pines Police Department has all the powers granted to a peace officer and a police officer of this State. These powers may be exercised only on property within the Ocean Pines community and not on any other property unless:
Engaged in fresh pursuit of a suspected offender;
Specially requested or permitted to do so in a political subdivision by its chief executive officer or its chief police officer;
By agreement with another law enforcement agency; or
Ordered to do so by the Governor.

The duties of the Chief shall include:
Being responsible for the efficiency and good conduct of the Department;
Overseeing the general operation of the Department;
Hiring employees and appointing officers, subject to the approval of the General Manager; and
Disciplining employees and officers.
